<article>
    <h1>How is milk de&#xAD;liv&#xAD;ered, ster&#xAD;ilised and stored?</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201207/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-07"><time>2020-12-07</time></a>
        - <span>SCIENCE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• The bank fol­lows in­ter­na­tional guide­lines set by the United King­dom’s Na­tional In­sti­tute for Health and Care Ex­cel­lence and the Hu­man Milk Bank­ing As­so­ci­a­tion of North Amer­ica.</p>
    <p>• All donor moth­ers un­dergo a blood test for dis­eases such as HIV, syphilis and hep­ati­tis B and C in­fec­tion. They can do­nate only if they lead healthy life­styles and do not en­gage in high-risk ac­tiv­i­ties such as smok­ing.</p>
    <p>• Those who take part ex­press milk at home and freeze it be­fore tak­ing it to the milk bank.</p>
    <p>• The milk is pas­teurised for half an hour at 62.5 deg C in the pas­teuriser, which kills bac­te­ria while re­tain­ing its nu­tri­tional ben­e­fits. It is then tested for bac­te­rial con­tam­i­na­tion.</p>
    <p>• The milk is then stored in the freezer un­til it is dis­pensed.</p>
    <p>•</p>

    <div>
        <picture>
            <img src="https://i.prcdn.co/img?regionKey=ZNnHuNsC%2fu6EtLeDIMxNXA%3d%3d" />
        </picture>
        <span role="byline"></span>
        <p data-role="text">At KK Hu&#xAD;man Milk Bank, the frozen pas&#xAD;teurised donor hu&#xAD;man milk can be kept in the freezer at -20 deg C for up to 90 days.&#xD;&#xA;The milk is pas&#xAD;teurised, sealed and stored be&#xAD;fore be&#xAD;ing dis&#xAD;pensed.</p>
